column5: It looks like a very cool coin!  Those "contractors" sound like they're scared of thier own shadow... ever heard of a google search buddy?
Some people just have no cents at all.
It does look cool. Supposed to hve been minted in 2004 (30 million of them). Wonder what the delay was in releasing it.

Awww, man, give it up with the conspiracy theories. It is a coin, minted to remember OUR Canadian war dead fer craps sakes. It is in honour of their sacrifice in the 2nd world war. If ya want a couple Joe, I gots about 50 of em.
Holy cow ... I hope the FBI and CIA don't find out about the couple I have.  I have some very strategically placed.
Ahh once again our paranoia peeks out!   Sometimes a coin is just a coin.   Bly
This is a real simpleton one, the Canadian version of American WMD's, just we call it Weapons of Cash Destruction, they must be some gullible.
You would think those army boys would just take it into a bank and ask a Canadian if it was lefit or not...
:lol   I guess I should not try to cross the border?????
HEY, they are all peace officers, just bring donuts   :lol:  :lol:
What is funny is that our government cannot barely get through the day without tripping over the carpet and someone is worried that we have secret spy-coins. Now thats funny.
All I can say is I give up...read my tag line. Joe
Is that the same intelligence agent that said there were WMD's in Iraq ??? Saw this story on Yahoo this morning and watched the video too. What a joke!
Time to put on those tin foil hats...
Sooooo see we are on to you all up North with the sending the cold weather down here plot and the coin that is a spy device.......   Art
